    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Consumed By Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Pamela Malone letter on July 16 issue on race in America describes herself as an individual rather than member of ethnic group</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>You have neatly sorted out consumer habits by race (July 16). Question: What am I? I bought both grits and cottage cheese when I lived in California; now I consume neither. I subscribed to Ebony in the 60's and read People now. Of the 43 grocery products mentioned, I don't even buy 23 of them. As for the other 20, I don't buy any of the brands listed. Answer: An individual.</p>
        <p>Pamela Malone  Leonia, N.J.</p>
      </block>
